1_16bxMyoL49mWYhcZKBYVBT5zEFW9SQpiao.body:
And for those who are totally clueless, when the Update Name dialog appears, click the [Custom Configuration] tab and use this template JSON sting to get your site on ZeroName.

Example: registering domain: mysitename       (NameCoin will auto-add the .bit for you)
{
    "name": {"formatted": "MySiteName.bit"},
    "bitcoin": {"address": ""},
    "zeronet": {"": "YourSiteStringGoesHere..EXample..1MgHVPCE1ve6QfKrgsqCURzRj72HrRWioz"},
    "ns": ["ns1.domaincoin.net", "ns2.domaincoin.net"]
}

If you fill the name, and zeronet address with your values, you can copy / paste it into the JSON string text box and it should be green and say valid.  Happy Sharing!

Edit: There is also a great guide here:
http://127.0.0.1:43110/1C5P1EcTZA6FDEg4w6SacfPjvSDCWmzeyt/?Home
